Advantages and Limitations of SVM

Discussed the strengths and weaknesses of the algorithm.

Advantages:

High prediction accuracy.
Effective for high-dimensional datasets.
Works well with clear class separation.
Robust against overfitting when properly tuned.

Limitations:

Computationally expensive for very large datasets.
Sensitive to parameter selection.
Requires feature scaling.
Difficult to interpret compared to Decision Trees.
